          </row>
        </tabular>
        <ol>
          <li>
            <p>
              If the club uses the plurality method,
              who will win the election?
              <answer>
                <p>
                  J
                </p>
              </answer>
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>
              If it were a head-to-head race between Irving and Joseph,
              who would win?
              <answer>
                <p>
                  I
                </p>
              </answer>
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>
              If it were a head-to-head race between Irving and Karl,
              who would win?
              <answer>
                <p>
                  \fbox I
                </p>
              </answer>
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>
              If it were a head-to-head race between Joseph and Karl,
              who would win?
              <answer>
                <p>
                  \fbox J
                </p>
              </answer>
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>
              Why does the plurality method's result seem unfair in this election?
              <answer>
                <p>
                  Irving defeats Joseph and Karl in head-to-head matches,
                  but Joseph wins via plurality.
                </p>
              </answer>
            </p>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        <em>Head-to-Head Criterion:</em>
        <answer>
          <p>
            A candidate who beats all the other candidates head to head should win the election.
          </p>
        </answer>
          <idx><h>criterion</h><h>head to head</h></idx>
      </p>
    </li>
