        </tabular>
        <ol>
          <li>
            <p>
              The school board votes using a Borda count.
              Which company will get the contract?
              <answer>
                <p>
                  <m>\begin{array}{clcr} A \amp 4+9+6+5 \amp =\amp 24 \\ B \amp 32+4 \amp =\amp 36 \\ C \amp 24+12+2 \amp =\amp 38 \\ D \amp 3+16+3 \amp =\amp 25 \end{array}</m> so C wins
                </p>
              </answer>
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>
              Does this seem fair?
              Why or why not?
              <answer>
                <p>
                  No; two-thirds of the voters picked B as their first choice! \else
                </p>
              </answer>
            </p>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </p>
    </li>
